text: Thomas Gorges, D.D. (13 February 160312 December 1667) was an English priest in the 17th century.Westminster Abbey Reniger was born in Wraxall, Somerset and educated at The Queen's College, OxfordAlumni Oxonienses 1500-1714, Gilpin-Greenhaugh He became a Fellow of All Souls, Oxford in 1629. He became Archdeacon of Winchester and a Canon of Westminster in 1661, holding both positions until his death. ==Notes== Category:1603 births Category:1667 deaths Category:People from Somerset Category:Archdeacons of Winchester (ancient) Category:Alumni of The Queen's College, Oxford
